    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Albright Restores Envoy's Status</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <dateline>WASHINGTON, Oct. 10</dateline>
      <abstract>
        <p>State Department restores security clearances of Amb to Israel Martin Indyk, allowing him to return fully to his work at embassy in Tel Aviv; Sec Madeleine Albright had suspended clearances over charges that Indyk mishandled classified material (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The State Department today restored the security clearances of the ambassador to Israel, Martin S. Indyk, letting him to return fully to his work at the embassy in Tel Aviv, officials said.</p>
        <p>Mr. Indyk, whose clearances Secretary of State Madeleine K. Albright suspended last month after the department said he had mishandled classified material, can now work on the Middle East crisis, the officials said.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The State Department today restored the security clearances of the ambassador to Israel, Martin S. Indyk, letting him to return fully to his work at the embassy in Tel Aviv, officials said.</p>
        <p>Mr. Indyk, whose clearances Secretary of State Madeleine K. Albright suspended last month after the department said he had mishandled classified material, can now work on the Middle East crisis, the officials said.</p>
        <p>As the crisis grew, Dr. Albright asked Mr. Indyk to meet Prime Minister Ehud Barak of Israel. Lacking clearances, Mr. Indyk sent reports to Washington as unclassified cables, officials said.</p>
      </block>
